"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-news-ecuador-leaves-defending-olympic-road-race-champion-richard-carapaz-off-team-for-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Jhonatan Narv\\u00e1ez to represent the country after controversial selection  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  The Ecuadorian Cycling Federation (FEC) announced on Monday that it has chosenJhonatan Narv\\u00e1ez(Ineos Grenadiers) for the single spot for theParis Olympic Gamesroad events over defending championRichard Carapaz.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 350, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuadorian_Cycling_Federation\", \"score\": 0.9999999997990017, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ecuadorian Cycling Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuadorian_Cycling_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuadorian_Cycling_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Narv\\u00e1ez will compete in both the time trial and road race in Paris.\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998209673482, \"rank\": 1.7903274612499924e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The FEC explained that it appointed the Ecuadorian representative \\\"as requested by the Ecuadorian Olympic Committee (COE),\\u00a0on the basis of\\u00a0federal autonomy and the regulations issued.\\\"\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"score\": 0.963723020974748, \"rank\": 0.03750015062885541, \"text\": \"Ecuadorian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\"}, {\"begin\": 714, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"score\": 0.963723020974748, \"rank\": 0.03750015062885541, \"text\": \"Ecuadorian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\"}, {\"begin\": 744, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Council_of_Europe\", \"score\": 0.9999999999708962, \"rank\": 2.8913741940964994e-11, \"text\": \"COE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Council_of_Europe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Council_of_Europe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement issued on social media last week, Carapaz decried \\\"a lack of transparency and fairness\\\" in the selection process, and that they were \\\"clearly biased and lack the fundamental principles of sports justice and equity.\\\"\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carapaz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, on Monday, Carapaz issued a video wishing Narva\\u00e9z luck in Paris and thanking his supporters.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carapaz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\"}, {\"begin\": 1112, \"end\": 1117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998209673482, \"rank\": 1.7903274612499924e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The FEC only released its selection criteria in March but used UCI points gained from January 1 to May 21, 2024, to choose the top-ranked rider.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999999998381099, \"rank\": 1.6200942143137e-10, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carapaz was ranked higher than Narv\\u00e1ez in the UCI rankings, which calculate points on a rolling 12-month calendar, but the situation was reversed in results taken only from this year.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999999998381099, \"rank\": 1.6200942143137e-10, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The EF Education First-EasyPost rider complained that the revision to the selection criteria came out after the start of the period to gain points had already begun.\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1587, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EF_Education_First\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.206731253140366e-33, \"text\": \"EF Education\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EF_Education_First\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EF_Education_First\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This should have been issued at the end of the Tokyo 2021 Olympic Games or at the end of last season when all athletes started with zero points and could plan our season equitably,\\\" Carapaz stated.\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999916776687, \"rank\": 4.332182314144098e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"However, its publication in an improvised manner and without room for manoeuvre seems to be designed to keep me out of Paris and exempt the president of the FEC from any responsibility.\\\"\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998209673482, \"rank\": 1.7903274612499924e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carapaz had appealed to the Ministry of Sport to intervene, but the FEC chose to finalise the selection before the request could be accepted.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, Carapaz became the first Ecuadorian athlete to win a gold medal in cycling at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2316, \"end\": 2326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"score\": 0.963723020974748, \"rank\": 0.03750015062885541, \"text\": \"Ecuadorian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He raced in Tokyo with Narv\\u00e1ez.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2395, \"end\": 2400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999916776687, \"rank\": 4.332182314144098e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This season, Carapaz won his national time trial championship, while Narv\\u00e1ez won the road race.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2429, \"end\": 2436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carapaz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carapaz finished second overall in the Tour Colombia andwon the final stage.\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He alsowon a stage of the Tour de Romandie.\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Romandie\", \"score\": 0.999952390297187, \"rank\": 4.758904108509162e-05, \"text\": \"Tour de Romandie\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Romandie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Romandie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Narv\\u00e1ez won the Down Under Classic and finished second in the Tour Down Under in January, and more recentlywon the opening stage of the Giro d'Italia.\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura Weislo is aCyclingnewsveteran of 20 years.\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2786, \"end\": 2791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Bush\", \"score\": 0.9999829569412096, \"rank\": 1.7041800703818158e-05, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Bush\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having joined in 2006, Laura extensively covered the Operacion Puerto doping scandal, the years-long conflict between the UCI and the Tour de France organisers ASO over the creation of the WorldTour, and the downfall of Lance Armstrong and his lifetime ban for doping.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2858, \"end\": 2863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Bush\", \"score\": 0.9999829569412096, \"rank\": 1.7041800703818158e-05, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Bush\"}, {\"begin\": 2888, \"end\": 2904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Operaci\\u00f3n_Puerto_doping_case\", \"score\": 0.9999999997394298, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Operacion Puerto\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Operaci\\u00f3n_Puerto_doping_case\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Operaci\\u00f3n_Puerto_doping_case\"}, {\"begin\": 2957, \"end\": 2960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999999998381099, \"rank\": 1.6200942143137e-10, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}, {\"begin\": 2969, \"end\": 2983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org